<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="fabs" id="fabs">fabs</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">fabs</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">double</span> arg<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction <code>fabs()</code> renvoie la valeur absolue de <code>arg</code>.
</p>

<p>
Le C++ founit également les implémentations suivantes :

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">fabs</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">float</span> arg<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à fabsf() en C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">fabs</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> arg<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à fabsl() en C99</span></pre>
<p>
Vous pouvez utiliser <code><a href="abs" class="wikilink1" title="fr:numeric:c:abs">abs()</a></code> à la place de <code>fabs()</code> en C++. En effet,
<code>abs</code> est surchargée pour permettre son utilisation avec des nombres flottants.
</p>

<p>
Sujets connexes : <a href="abs" class="wikilink1" title="fr:numeric:c:abs">abs</a>, <a href="fmod" class="wikilink1" title="fr:numeric:c:fmod">fmod</a>, <a href="labs" class="wikilink1" title="fr:numeric:c:labs">labs</a>
</p>

